about.summary: A programmatic interface to various 'SNP' 'datasets' on the web: 'OpenSNP' (<https://opensnp.org>), and 'NBCIs' 'dbSNP' database (<https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/projects/SNP>). Functions are included for searching for 'NCBI'. For 'OpenSNP', functions are included for getting 'SNPs', and data for 'genotypes', 'phenotypes', annotations, and bulk downloads of data by user.

name: r-rsnps
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.3.0' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-rsnps
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/rsnps_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/rsnps/rsnps_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: b26bab78807c34f57f56a0f2ce17300a18bae90c78ae8b8440e0d87df143a5fa

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-xml
    - r-crul >=0.5.2
    - r-data.table
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-plyr
    - r-stringr
    - r-xml2
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-xml
    - r-crul >=0.5.2
    - r-data.table
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-plyr
    - r-stringr
    - r-xml2

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('rsnps')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('rsnps')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/ropensci/rsnps
  license: MIT
  summary: 'A programmatic interface to various ''SNP'' ''datasets'' on the web: ''OpenSNP''
    (<https://opensnp.org>), and ''NBCIs'' ''dbSNP'' database (<https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/projects/SNP>).
    Functions are included for searching for ''NCBI''. For ''OpenSNP'', functions are
    included for getting ''SNPs'', and data for ''genotypes'', ''phenotypes'', annotations,
    and bulk downloads of data by user.'
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT'
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
